   This is a modal window. Beginning of dialog window. Escape will cancel and close the window. End of dialog window. EFF councillor Zilindili Vena earlier told council that the party would not support the African National Congress (ANC) getting through the back door if the motion was to succeed.  “We will never support crooks like Andile Lungisa. Athol Trollip will get his day just not today,” said Vena.  The African National Congress (ANC) and minority parties which included the PA, the United Democratic Movement (UDM), the United Front (UF), and the African Independent Congress (AIC) voted for the motion with a total of 54 votes.  While the DA, together with its coalition partners, the Congress of the People (Cope), the African Christian Democratic Party (ACDP) in addition to the EFF voted against the motion with a total of 65 votes.  
