   This is a modal window. Beginning of dialog window. Escape will cancel and close the window. End of dialog window. Following the much anticipated outcome on Wednesday evening, the EFF’s provincial coordinator Yazini Tetyana told the media that the party had to support the DA. “In 2016 the EFF took a decision at the highest level to support the DA. We are still standing by that. We are not going to allow the ANC to take back the metro. People of the metro gave power to the DA they needed our support,” said Tetyana.  Daniels, however, said he was not surprised by the outcome, adding that the failed bid to have Trollip ousted was not a complete waste of time.  “It’s not a failure because at least the cat is out of the bag. We were always sceptical of the EFF, who claim they are an opposition but yet are in coalition unofficially so with the DA. 
